parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keyless access unit can cause the alarm system to malfunction, leading to unintended activations, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The alarm system sounds off unexpectedly
the key access remotes do not respond to commands properly
the vehicle makes electrical circuit noises
and the dashboard flashes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear view camera can increase the risk of accidents, especially when reversing, as the driver may not be able to see objects or people behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The rear view camera screen is black
the camera does not display an image
the wiring harness is damaged
and the camera occasionally works but then fails again.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause unintended braking, window malfunctions, and other electrical issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The windows roll up and down independently
the vehicle brakes unexpectedly
and the horn engages unintendedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear-View Camera Failure due to Wiring Harness Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear-view camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing, particularly in situations where visibility is limited.
symptoms: The rear-view camera screen displays a black image
the camera image is distorted or intermittent
the camera fails to operate
or the guidelines are visible but the camera image is not.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall repair parts can delay or prevent necessary repairs, potentially leading to continued safety risks.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are unavailable
or the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injector system can cause a strong smell of gasoline, fuel gauge needle to fall closer to empty, and engine stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline
fuel gauge needle falls closer to empty
engine stalls
slow downs to dangerous speed on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cap-less fuel filler system can cause water to accumulate and freeze, making it difficult or impossible to refuel the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Water enters between the flaps on the fuel filler
outer flap freezes
fueling cannot be performed until the ice is removed
water streaming out of the outer flap
ice build-up in the fuel filler neck
inability to refuel
fuel contamination in warm months with engine failure.
